 SALES AND MARKETING REPORTING \u2022 Updating of SQL sourced reports on a daily and monthly basis. This involves updating the reports, refreshing from SQL database, verifying and reviewing of data and distribution of the reports, Examples of the reports are as follows: \u2022 Daily Sales \u2022 Regional Sales Analysis \u2022 IOEC Monthly report \u2022 Returns and Value Claims \u2022 Export Monthly Sales \u2022 KPI tracker \u2022 KVI tracker \u2022 Dunnhumby reporting 4. PRESENTATIONS, REPORTS, MEETINGS AND EVENT \u2022 Compiling and assisting of Strategy Booklet \u2022 Compiling and assisting Presentations for AVI Head Office \u2022 Compiling and assisting of budget pre-read and presentations for AVI Exec directors. Summary of the above pack for AVI Non-Exec Board Members \u2022 Summary of compiling and assisting presentations for ad-hoc meetings as well as business unit staff update sessions \u2022 Compiling and assisting of risk packs including minutes \u2022 Planning and co-ordination of all staff functions, year-end function special events and management meetings 5. FINANCE ADMINISTRATION \u2022 Reconciliation and payment of all Expense Claims for entire AVI International team \u2022 Creating RQ, PO and GRN on SAP for Finance and Marketing \u2022 Follow-up on suppliers for invoices for month end \u2022 Ensuring the Credacc portal is updated on a weekly basis for queries from Accounts Payable on any invoices \u2022 Feedback of payment on supplier invoices \u2022 Draft and maintain policies pertaining to AVI International Finance Administration processes, as well as implementation and execution of related processes \u2022 Facilitate Standard Bank Corporate Card Applications for all new employees \u2022 Contacting Standard Bank weekly to ensure the cards are open for International travel \u2022 Forex arranging with AVI Head Office and Forex recons are completed after each international trip \u2022 Control and administration for Forex 6. GENERAL OFFICE ADMINISTRATION \u2022 Facilitate new suppliers and customers \u2022 Communicate once the accounts have been opened to both RGM, Logistics and Vendor \u2022 Creating of new workflows for new laptops etc. \u2022 Disposal workflows for old laptops etc. \u2022 Reception duties for front office (Clients, customers, and deliveries) \u2022 Arranging with RGM and mailroom for posting of items to customers \u2022 Stationery, printer toner and paper, laptop and other computer equipment ordering and controlling \u2022 Manage and maintain movements of workstations and laptops. \u2022 Ensuring the asset register is kept up to date for each employee \u2022 Reporting of repairs and general office house-keeping \u2022 Arrange with ITSS for new laptop phone desk stationery set up for new employee \u2022 Health and Safety Registers are completed on a monthly basis and attend meetings on a monthly basis \u2022 Refreshments for management meetings as and when required \u2022 Printing and Binding of documents for Exco Competencies Problem Solver \u2022 Attention to Detail \u2022 Energetic \u2022 Influence People \u2022 Relating and networking \u2022 Flexible and open to change \u2022 Resilient and composed Experience Required At least 5 years\u2019 Office Support experience of which at least 3 years in a senior office function supporting multiple executives. Minimum Qualifications Required Grade 12 A completed qualification related to Secretarial/Office Administration essential Knowledge Required Sound MS Office proficiency especially Word and PowerPoint Typesetting and document formatting experience Working knowledge of SAP required Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
